      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ شِرَاءِ اَلْقَمَارِيِّ بِمَكَّةَ وَ اَلْمَدِينَةِ فَقَالَ «مَا أُحِبُّ أَنْ يُخْرَجَ مِنْهَا شَيْءٌ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2358 - Safwan narrated from Al-'Ays ibn Al-Qasim, who said:\nI asked Abu Abdullah (as) about purchasing doves in Mecca and Medina.\nImam (as) said: \"I do not like that anything be taken out from them.\""
        ]
      }
